item.title: 20221218 Newsletter
item.content:encoded:
—! News

TiddlyDesktop v0.0.15 released

TiddlyDesktop is an app for working with TiddlyWiki files (both TiddlyWikiClassic and TiddlyWiki version 5). It can be installed on Windows, Mac OS X or Linux. It is compatible with TiddlyWiki version 5 and the older TiddlyWikiClassic.

From the introduction here <–Includes a short video

TiddlyWiki v5.2.4 has been released!

"You can upgrade your existing single file wikis here:

https://tiddlywiki.com/upgrade.html

For Node.js users, the new version is available on npm at https://www.npmjs.com/package/tiddlywiki

As usual, please exercise caution when upgrading, and take care to keep backup copies of everything important.

I’d like to thank everyone who has contributed to this release. We’re keeping up a decent pace of releases at the moment and it’s great to see so many people involved.

Any questions or comments are welcome here, or via GitHub." Jeremy Ruston

From his announcement here

—! Articles —! Plugins

BASIC Anywhere Machine Demos

Charlie Venoit has post videos demoing the BASIC Anywhere Machine he's been working on.

  • BASIC Anywhere Machine feature in the works: Update your downloaded BAM instance via drag and drop
  • BASIC Anywhere Machine feature in the works: copying your preferences and settings to another BAM
  • BASIC Anywhere Machine feature in the works: vertically scrolling menus
  • BASIC Anywhere Machine and Android: why are the BAM menus not showing until we scroll down a bit?

For more information on his project see Tiddlywiki on Google Groups

Favorites Plugin updated to 4.8.0

by Mohammad Rahmani

  • [NEW] Updated to Tiddlywiki 5.2.4
  • [NEW] Option to add folder at the top or bottom of folder list
  • [NEW] The link title for every folder is customizable.
  • [NEW] The link title for items can be customized globally
  • [FIXED] WikiWords (e.g. links by CamelCase) are now disabled in the folder title. The below tiddlers updated
    • $:/plugins/kookma/favorites/templates/folder-title-edit
    • $:/plugins/kookma/favorites/templates/folder-title-view
  • [FIXED] Empty caption field for folder is handled correctly now.
  • [FIXED] On bulk add/append, items are removed from old folders if any

Discussion here

WizardNav Plugin: Initial Release

by Scott Sauyet

With help from many wonderful people here, I’ve created my first plugin.

It adds previous/next links to tiddlers whose tags themselves have the tag “Wizard” (name configurable.)

Discussion here

—! Tips & Tricks

Div Discussion in Discord

Discord Users Emily#2362 & intrinsical#0482 help out by explaining and showing how to use the div html tag in the case of building a table-top rpg character sheet in Tiddlywiki.

Easy Next, Previous, First and Last TAGGED on the tag pill

by Anthony Muscio

"Folks,

I just added another item to my “reimagine tags collection”, this time it provides one of up to 4 buttons on any tag pill drop down to the Next, Previous, First and Last."

Deeper discussion here

item.title: 20221204 Newsletter
item.content:encoded:
—! News

Tiddlywiki.com Homepage Updated

"A significant update to TiddlyWiki's homepage to draw more attention to community fundraising, and to the nascent marketplace for commercial products and services around TiddlyWiki."

Further details here

—! Articles

Tiddlywiki how-to articles in Japanese

"I no longer take notes that I write by hand on paper, but instead I love TiddlyWiki, so I'd like to explain in detail how to take notes on TiddlyWiki and how to use them." by Dajya Ranger (Browser-based Translation)

Direct Link to Articles

Tiddlywiki used in an Academic Paper

"Using the plugin TiddlyMap the relevant “elementary facts” were edited at the same time as the individual topological graph, resulting in an interactive network representation of the feedback."

Source

—! Plugins

Go To Shortcut Plugin Update Released

By Maurycy

"A very powerful quick search/goto mechanism that you access in a fraction of a second fully through the keyboard."

Discussion here

Tekan - Trello style kanban board plugin for Tiddlywiki

Click on the overlapping circles in the upper right corner to switch back and forth between views.

Tiddlybucket

By Andrés Pérez

"Just want to let y’all know about my port of the TiddlyWeb backend API that can directly read and write tiddler files to AWS S3 buckets and Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Storage buckets."

Discussion here

WhiteBoard plugin V0.2.3 Debuted

By Lin Onetwo

Read more on talk.tiddlywiki.org here and on Github.

—! Tips & Tricks

How to host curated Tiddlywikis on Tiddlyhost

"If you have a custom TiddlyWiki setup that you maintain and would like to share with others via Tiddlyhost, please see these new docs about how to do it.

And if you want to see the currently available editions, browse the templates list here. As you can see there’s not much there yet since this a brand new feature, but I’m hoping that will change over time.

Ps, thanks everyone for the feedback on the previous post about cloning support. This new templates feature came from the “what about cloning other people’s sites” discussion there." - Simon

Discussion here

How to reduce the size of your Tiddlywiki

There are many reasons servers & services may limit file upload size. Télumire posted a Tips & Tricks to help. More on the conversation here on Discord
